[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " While Peter and John"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " were speaking to the people, the priests and the commander"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of the temple guard"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and the Sadducees"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " came up"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to them, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " angry"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " because they were teaching the people and announcing"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in Jesus the resurrection of the dead. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " they seized"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " them and put them in jail"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " until the next day (for it was already evening). "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But many of those who had listened to"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the message"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " believed, and the number of the men"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " came to about five thousand."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " On the next day,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " their rulers, elders, and experts in the law"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " came together"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in Jerusalem."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Annas the high priest was there, and Caiaphas, John, Alexander, and others who were members of the high priest’s family."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " After"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " making Peter and John"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " stand in their midst, they began to inquire, “By what power or by what name"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " did you do this?” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Peter, filled with the Holy Spirit,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Rulers of the people and elders,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " if"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " we are being examined"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " today for a good deed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " done to a sick man – by what means this man was healed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " – "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " let it be known to all of you and to all the people of Israel that by the name of Jesus Christ"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the Nazarene whom you crucified, whom God raised from the dead, this man stands before you healthy. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " This Jesus"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "the stone that was rejected by"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " you,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "the builders, that has become the cornerstone"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And there is salvation in no one else, for there is no other name under heaven given among people"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " by which we must"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " be saved.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When they saw the boldness"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of Peter and John, and discovered"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " that they were uneducated"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and ordinary"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " men, they were amazed and recognized these men had been with Jesus. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And because they saw the man who had been healed standing with them, they had nothing to say against this."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But when they had ordered them to go outside the council,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " they began to confer with one another, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " saying, “What should we do with these men? For it is plain"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to all who live in Jerusalem that a notable miraculous sign"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has come about through them,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and we cannot deny it. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But to keep this matter from spreading any further among the people, let us warn them to speak no more"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to anyone in this name.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And they called them in and ordered"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " them not to speak or teach at all in the name"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of Jesus. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But Peter and John replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Whether it is right before God to obey"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " you rather than God, you decide, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for it is impossible"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for us not to speak about what we have seen and heard.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " After threatening them further, they released them, for they could not find how to punish them on account of the people, because they were all praising"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " God for what had happened. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For the man, on whom this miraculous sign"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of healing had been performed,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " was over forty years old."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When they were released, Peter and John"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " went to their fellow believers"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and reported everything the high priests and the elders had said to them. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When they heard this, they raised their voices to God with one mind"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and said, “Master of all,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " you who made the heaven, the earth,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the sea, and everything that is in them, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " who said by the Holy Spirit through"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your servant David our forefather,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "‘"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "Why do the nations"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " rage,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "and the peoples plot foolish"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " things?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "The kings of the earth stood together,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "and the rulers assembled together,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "against the Lord and against his"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "Christ"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “For indeed both Herod and Pontius Pilate, with the Gentiles and the people of Israel, assembled together in this city against"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your holy servant Jesus, whom you anointed,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to do as much as your power"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and your plan"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " had decided beforehand"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " would happen. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And now, Lord, pay attention to"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " their threats, and grant"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to your servants"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to speak your message"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " with great courage,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " while you extend your hand to heal, and to bring about miraculous signs"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and wonders through the name of your holy servant Jesus.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " they had prayed, the place where they were assembled together was shaken,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and they were all filled with the Holy Spirit and began to speak"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the word of God"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " courageously."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The group of those who believed were of one heart and mind,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and no one said that any of his possessions was his own, but everything was held in common."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " With"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " great power the apostles were giving testimony"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to the resurrection of the Lord Jesus, and great grace was on them all. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For there was no one needy"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " among them, because those who were owners of land or houses were selling"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " them"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and bringing the proceeds from the sales "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and placing them at the apostles’ feet. The proceeds"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " were distributed to each, as anyone had need. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Joseph, a Levite who was a native of Cyprus, called by the apostles Barnabas (which is translated “son of encouragement”),"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " sold"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " a field"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " that belonged to him and brought the money"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and placed it at the apostles’ feet."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]